parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to become stuck or unable to move, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The transmission makes a whining or grinding noise
the vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate
the transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle is unable to shift gears
the transmission fluid is black or dirty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle's lights, radio, and other accessories to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or inconvenience.
symptoms: The internal lights do not come on when the doors are opened
the radio does not change stations
the reception is poor and comes and goes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driveshaft can cause the vehicle to lose power and become stuck, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The driveshaft falls off
the vehicle makes a clicking sound
the front and rear tires on the passenger side rub against something.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unattended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly
without warning
and may not respond to braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing safety risks and financial losses.
symptoms: The engine oil level drops rapidly
requiring frequent additions
and may be accompanied by engine sludge
stalling
and illumination of the check engine light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and financial losses.
symptoms: The transmission may slip
hesitate
or fail to engage gears
leading to sudden loss of power and control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle and solenoid issues can cause unattended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The throttle may stick or malfunction
causing the vehicle to accelerate suddenly
and may be accompanied by illumination of the check engine light and VSC and TRAC OFF lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks and rust can cause engine failure, safety risks, and financial losses.
symptoms: Oil leaks may occur due to rusted transmission lines
and may be accompanied by engine failure
stalling
and illumination of the check engine light.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities
despite the severity of the impact warranting deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Airbag Wiring and ECM Circuit Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improperly secured airbag wiring and ECM circuits can cause the airbags to malfunction or fail to deploy, leading to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Error codes B1140 and B1141 are displayed
indicating issues with the right-hand and left-hand side airbag sensor assemblies
respectively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can lead to loss of control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities, which can be exacerbated by the failure of the airbags to deploy.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently
resulting in loss of control
accidents
and injuries or fatalities
with the airbags failing to deploy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without input from the driver
often when the vehicle is slowing down or coming to a stop. The engine RPMs may increase rapidly
and the vehicle may lunge forward or jump over obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the throttle cable or linkage can cause sudden unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents.
symptoms: The throttle cable or linkage may become bent or stuck
causing the engine to rev suddenly and the vehicle to accelerate rapidly. The driver may experience difficulty stopping the vehicle
and the engine may continue to idle at high RPMs even after the vehicle has been stopped.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal or Hydraulic System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake pedal or hydraulic system can cause loss of braking ability, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle may not stop or slow down as expected. The driver may experience difficulty stopping the vehicle
and the vehicle may lunge forward or accelerate suddenly.
